<page_title>Auto-resizing an embedded component when the parent window resizes</page_title>
<text> Auto-resizing an embedded component when the parent window resizes

When you insert an embedded component, you sometimes want it to be able to self-adjust its size as the parent window is resized (similar to a HTML table). You can do this by setting the width (or height) to be a number between 0 and 1 in the customization dialog window, for example, in the dialog window for customizing a HTML text box (as is shown below):

  

When the &quot;Set width&quot; and &quot;Set height&quot; fields take integers, the inputs will become the text box&apos;s actual size. Any input between 0 and 1 will be regarded as relative to the hosting window. The result of the above settings is shown below:

 

You can resize the window now to see if the text box resizes as well.


